CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 26, 1945, pg. 13 reads: "The Ole Ball Game - approximately three thousand hometown rooters saw Gus Greenlee's Pittsburgh Crawfords return to "big-time" baseball at Forbes Field last Sunday afternoon. The local boys split a doubleheader with the Brooklyn Brown Dodgers - Courier Photo by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Baseball game between Brooklyn Brown Dodgers and Pittsburgh Crawfords, viewed from section 12 of Forbes Field stands, with "Buy War Bonds" sign on outfield fence
